Package ca.corefacility.gview.layout.prototype

Provides implementations of different "prototype" shapes.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BackbonePinnable Describes something that can be "pinned" to a particular location on the backbone, so that it always stays there no matter the zoom level.
SequencePoint A point in terms of sequence coordinates (base, heightFromBackbone).
 

Class Summary
BackboneShape Describes a shape that is layed out along the Backbone and which can stretch/shrink on zoom levels.
CompositeShape A Backbone shape that can be composed from two different backbone shapes, and controls switching between them at certain zoom levels.
NonFragmentingStretchableShape A shape which can stretch itself along the backbone on receiving an event.
PinnableShape Describes a shape that can be pinned to a location on the backbone and will stick there on zooming.
SequenceOffset Defines a SequencePoint which has an offset (in terms of length on map) from the sequence point.
SequencePointImp Defines a single point on the sequence.
